definition.value: The dianion of a fatty acyl monophosphate compound arising from deprotonation of both phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of 7-hydroxyisoflavones that is 7-hydroxyisoflavone which is substituted by an additional hydroxy group at the 3' position and a methoxy group at the 4' position.
A C4-dicarboxylate resuting from deprotonation of both carboxy groups of dihydroxyfumaric acid.
An optically active form of idonate having L-configuration; major species at pH 7.3.
